<ol class="breadcrumb">
	<li><a href="#"><i class="fa fa-home"></i>Home</a></li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-chalkboard"></i>Tutorial</li>
</ol>

<div class="content">
	<p><%= application.name %> makes it easy to generate, manage, and share images.  Here's how: </p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2>Select Working Folder (Optional)</h2>
			<p><%= application.name %> lets you create folders to organize your images to make them easier to manage.  Before you create new images, you can select a working folder or you can just use your home folder. To select a working folder, double-click a folder on the sidebar or click "Open > File" on the menu bar to open a file browser dialog. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/01-select-folder.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Select Working Folder"><img src="images/info/tutorial/01-select-folder.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Select Working Folder</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Click Generate</h2>
			<p>Click the "Generate" button on the top toolbar. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/02-click-generate.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Click Generate"><img src="images/info/tutorial/02-click-generate.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Click Generate</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Enter Prompt</h2>
			<p>Enter a prompt and select an image generator to use. When you create a new generated image, your prompt and information about the image generator used is embedded in the image metadata and displayed with the image so you never lose information about how your generated image was created. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/03-enter-prompt.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Enter Prompt"><img src="images/info/tutorial/03-enter-prompt.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Enter Prompt</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Select Model (Optional)</h2>
			<p>Select an AI model from the list of image generators. Choose from stability.ai, OpenAI, DeepAI, and more.</p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/04-select-model.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Select Model"><img src="images/info/tutorial/04-select-model.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Select Model</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Select Image Size (Optional)</h2>
			<p>Select an image size and aspect ratio from the set of avaiable options. Choose from square, portrait, or landscape aspect ratios to select an aspect ratio that matches your subject. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/05-select-image-size.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Select Image Size"><img src="images/info/tutorial/05-select-image-size.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Select Image Size</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Select Style (Optional)</h2>
			<p>Select a rendering style from the list of style presets.  Styles include options such as "photographic", "anime", "fantasy", "cinematic" and more. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/06-select-style.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Select Style"><img src="images/info/tutorial/06-select-style.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Select Style</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Set Advanced Parameters (Optional)</h2>
			<p>You can set advance parameters to acheive greater control over the image generation process. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/07-set-advanced-params.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Set Advanced Parameters"><img src="images/info/tutorial/07-set-advanced-params.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Set Advanced Parameters</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Add Negative Prompts (Optional)</h2>
			<p>You can add negative prompts to direct the image generator to avoid certain features. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/08-add-negative-prompts.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Add Negative Prompts"><img src="images/info/tutorial/08-add-negative-prompts.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Add Negative Prompts</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Share!</h2>
			<p>Once you have generated an image that you like, simply click "Share" on the top menu bar to select a means of sharing.  You can share images in a variety of ways such as the file, sharing by discussion topic post, sharing by direct message, by link, or by email. For this example, we will share by discussion topic. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/09-click-share.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Share"><img src="images/info/tutorial/09-click-share.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Share</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Select Topic</h2>
			<p>Select a discussion topic to use to share your image.  Choosing an appropriate discussion topic will make it easier for others to find your image.  If you don't see an appropriate discussion topic, you can create a new one. Public discussion posts will also be visible in the public image gallery. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/10-select-topic.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Select Topic"><img src="images/info/tutorial/10-select-topic.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Select Topic</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Enter Comment</h2>
			<p>Enter a comment or description to go along with your image.  What does this image mean to you or what do you think makes it special? </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/11-enter-comment.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Enter Comment"><img src="images/info/tutorial/11-enter-comment.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Enter Comment</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Click Post</h2>
			<p>Click the "Post" button.  Your image and comment will be added to the discussion topic and will also be visible in the public image gallery. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/12-click-post.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="Click Post"><img src="images/info/tutorial/12-click-post.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Click Post</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2>Visit the Public Image Gallery</h2>
			<p>Your image will now be visible in the <a href="#gallery">public image gallery</a>.  If you log out and click "Gallery" on the header bar, you should see your image. </p>
			
			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/tutorial/13-view-gallery.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" rel="process" title="View Gallery"><img src="images/info/tutorial/13-view-gallery.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">View Gallery</div>
			</div>
		</li>
	</ol>
</div>